<item>
            <title>[CAMEL-10635] camel-mongodb-gridfs - The component should not store state</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-10635</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The component is wrong at&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/camel/blob/master/components/camel-mongodb-gridfs/src/main/java/org/apache/camel/component/gridfs/GridFsComponent.java#L42&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/camel/blob/master/components/camel-mongodb-gridfs/src/main/java/org/apache/camel/component/gridfs/GridFsComponent.java#L42&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Where it stores the first looked up client and store that for remainder. So if there are other endpoints referring to other clients then that wont work as the db is not null next time.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Instead the client should be looked up per endpoint and not stored as state on the component.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
